  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6599.64 sitting between the max negative gamma wall at 6590 (-9023.7M) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+16033.6M), dealers are in active hedging mode as spot hovers near the critical pivot zone. The PIN regime with 19.3B in total GEX suggests dealers will sell any rally toward 6605-6610 (massive +16B and +11.8B walls) while providing support if we drift toward 6590. The recent wall break detection and GEX surge indicate we're seeing dynamic repositioning, but the thick positive gamma ceiling above should cap upside momentum and compress volatility.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect tight range-bound action between 6590-6610 with dealers capping moves in both directions.",
